SONA: The Carja do not impress me.
SONA: To build so tall is to invite the fate of the ancients.

0:38:05.000,0:38:09.860
SONA: We will stand tall for we are the strength of the Nora!

0:38:10.199,0:38:11.788
SONA: Your fight is ours, you know it to be so.

0:38:35.269,0:38:38.869
NAMMAN: O Great Sun, how does your gaze fall?

0:38:39.420,0:38:40.690
NAMMAN: In approval or reproach?

0:38:43.119,0:38:51.039
NAMMAN: Turn our heads with your daily pilgrimage, from the east where we came, to the west where only you may go.

0:38:51.420,0:39:14.349
NAMMAN: You grant cold metal the warmth of life and let the machines bask in Your great shining.
NAMMAN: For You the shadows shrink and part and gather again only at Your allowance, without form.
NAMMAN: Your eyes the day, your ears the priests, your lips the Radiant Sun-King.
NAMMAN: As there was before and will be again, Your Light.

0:39:19.289,0:39:22.780
Namman, I should have known if there was gonna be a Sun Priest here it would be you.

0:39:22.820,0:39:29.070
And if the Sun-King had allowed outlanders to set foot upon the Alight, this "Aloy" could only be you.

0:39:30.349,0:39:35.530
I wish the circumstances were different, or that the Psalms of the Sun could give you peace of mind.

0:39:36.070,0:39:40.159
But if you allow me one pontification…?
Go ahead.

0:39:40.360,0:39:45.030
You've shown strength and compassion, our enemies only a desperate hate.

0:39:45.510,0:39:52.869
Both sides claim the blessing of the Sun, but the Sun that I pray to?
He would bestow it upon yours.

0:39:53.349,0:39:59.860
You know, Namman, I'm already under some pretty heavy divine pressure, but I'll try to live up to it.

0:39:59.920,0:40:02.260
The tribes united against shadow, how could that not be the Sun's will?

0:40:10.309,0:40:15.320
NAMMAN: From what I could gather the Nora believe their Goddess chose them for a fated battle.

0:40:30.210,0:40:31.099
BRAVE: It is an honour.

0:40:32.610,0:40:33.038
VARL: Greetings, Aloy.

0:40:34.719,0:40:35.599
Don't.

0:40:35.710,0:40:36.518
You don't need to bow, The Anointed doesn't like it.

0:40:38.110,0:40:41.230
She doesn't much like being called anointed either.

0:40:42.000,0:40:44.070
It means a lot to have you here, Varl.

0:40:44.230,0:40:45.519
I gave my word.

0:40:45.760,0:40:48.889
So, Meridian, what do you think?

0:40:48.960,0:40:53.230
I've seen many new things since I first met you.

0:40:54.219,0:40:56.398
I should thank you.

0:40:56.400,0:40:57.380
Varl, what's wrong?

0:40:57.570,0:40:58.880
You really want to know?

0:41:00.519,0:41:01.429
Alright.

0:41:02.610,0:41:06.458
I'm in a foreign land, a tainted land, defending a faithless city.
that looks like nothing I've seen, from something I can't imagine.

0:41:11.250,0:41:17.838
